<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-29T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-29T16:00:00-05:00" n="224" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d224">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/19<hi rend="superscript">13/14</hi>: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-29T18:00:00-03:00">October 29, 1940—6 p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October
                                        29—5:37 p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>248. My 241, October 22, 2 p.m. Lieutenant Colonel Christian and
                                    Captain Brereton leave today for Buenos Aires, the former
                                    proceeding tomorrow by air for the United States.</p>
                                <p>The conversations here have been highly satisfactory. Future
                                    developments, however, and the maintenance of the existing
                                    cordial attitude on the part of Uruguay as regards cooperation
                                    with the <pb facs="0183" n="171" xml:id="pg_171"/> United States
                                    in questions of continental defense will depend in large measure
                                    upon our willingness and ability to make available to Uruguay
                                    certain essential military and naval material.</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>